      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "UNCLE TONY (5) is going well having yet to miss the top-three this time in. Overcame a second row draw to win two back at this circuit and distance then raced parked and fought well to go under by a head last time. Can atone. Hard to knock the form of DUAL CAM (1) who backs up after cruising home by 23 metres at Marburg on Sunday, giving him three wins and a close second from his last four starts. Likely to get the favours from the inside draw so could strike again. WARRAWEE FLYER (2) draws well and comes right into contention after scoring last start by 1.2 metres at this circuit and distance. HARPERVILLE (8) draws for a trail and must be considered after she missed narrowly last start.",
